Although  interpreters  can  help the communication between deaf and hearing persons, they are often expensive and have  negative  effect  on  independency  and  privacy.

Note  writing  is  used  by  many  deaf  people  to  communicate  with  someone  who  is  seated  nearby,  but  it  is  awkward  while  
walking, standing at a distance, and when more than two persons are in a conversation. 



